tip.text: Very good.  Steak melts in your mouth.   Béarnaise is excellent with a subtle flavor. That said, I prefer Le Relais simply because of that glorious sauce.
Standard Chinese food.  Decent, but nothing great. Good for family occasions.
Stayed in Woking for 5 nights, ate at the Red Lion for 3 nights.  Excellent atmosphere and outstanding food.  Simply delicious. Try the sea bream, calves liver, lamb or the baked camembert.
Chocolate lovers dream, especially the hot chocolate!! OMG!  Yum!!
Succulent pulled pork.   The sauces are the best part as they are kinda of a bit tomatoey and spiced to just the right amount. While the pork is excellent, the sauce takes it to another level.
Great cocktails, especially their old fashioned. Classic institution.
Good atmosphere and very good food.   Squid and peas dish was superb.  Seating system is a bit annoying.
Great food.  Really enjoyed it.  This is a go to spot for Lebanese/ME food.
Great food!  Talk about comfort food.  Chicken pie and the trout were excellent.  Big open space with nice size tables for groups. Solid beer selection. Definitely a neighborhood place though.
This is probably my favorite lunch-on-the-go place in HK.  My favorite is the tonkatsu korrito and the crab salad role.  Food is fresh and delicious.

tip.text: Favorite restaurant in Hong Kong! Everything on the menu is glorious, inspired, and creative. The vibe is excellent, the service is five star, and the shochu selection is deep. KFC and the ox tongue!
Hong Kong institution.  Order the T-bone slathered in Sammy's sauce.  Love coming here for the nostalgia.  Always enjoyable. Comfort food.
It's all about the sauces!  Chicken is done just right. Nice atmosphere. We need more of these around the world. #thenewfastfood
Outstanding coffee and expert knowledge.  Great place to chill too.
"A dozen cronuts please. Sorry whats that? For a large group? Nope. Just bring out a tray of 12 and one dish as they are all for myself." Holy fuck these are good!
Excellent tapas.  The food is more rich than your ordinary tapas, so be prepared and order a couple lighter dishes.  The queue system they have is a joke however. Please fix!  Photo: Rabbit shoulder
Fish and chips are superb.  Not oily at all like a lot of places.  Bottomless chips are a nice touch if you can eat a lot.
The freshest sushi in Hong Kong. There is no debate. Kenjo-san is meticulous in is selection and preparation of fish.  Kenjo-san is a true master his trade. It's truly an honor to be served by him.
